                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "**The request was not successful**. Invalid ExtractRequest object has been sent, there are some reasons why this error may happen:\n  * `Content-Type` header is different from **application/json**;\n  * `documentIds` property was not provided in the request;\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                },
                "example": {
                  "error": {
                    "statusCode": 400,
                    "message": "Message with the reason why RequestObject is invalid",
                    "name": "Error"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "**The request was not successful**. Unauthorized request has been sent. It may happen due to the following reasons:\n  * You forgot to specify `access_token` query parameter or `authorization` cookie argument with the value of your API key;\n  * Your API key has been disabled by organziation owner;\n  * Your API key has been revoked by admin;\n  * You make the request from IP that is not specified in the IP's whitelist in the API key's settings.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/documents/{documentId}/file": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "get file with result after recognition",
        "description": "## WARNING! The endpoint has been officially deprecated. Please use a /v2 version of this endpoint.\nThis method may be used to retrieve document in the convenient format. Please note:\n1. **json** file format is not supported intentionally, in order to get document in the format of json, use `/documents/status` endpoint. \n2. this endpoint return static set of fields at this point. For **dataSource** equal to **singleFields** the following fields will be returned: uploadDate, supplierName, vatNumber, filename ,invoiceNumber, invoiceDateEpoch, invoiceDueDateEpoch, invoiceTotal, invoiceSubtotal, invoiceTax, template, userDocumentType, currencyCode. For the **lineItems** value of **dataSource** the following fields will be returned along with all columns in the line items: invoiceNumber, invoiceDateEpoch, invoiceDueDateEpoch, supplierName, currencyCode. Moreover, from the fields returned in the response, some of the fields are formatted as dates using fromat `D MMM YYYY hh:mm`, for **singleFields**: uploadDate, invoiceDateEpoch, invoiceDueDateEpoch. For **lineItems**: invoiceDateEpoch, invoiceDueDateEpoch.\n  \n",
        "tags": [
          "Document Endpoints"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "in": "header",
            "name": "Content-Type",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": [
                "application/json"
              ]
            },
            "required": true
          },
          {
            "in": "path",
            "name": "documentId",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentsDownloadFileByIdDocumentId"
            },
            "required": true,
            "description": "a number with id of document that will be returned. You can get id using **/documents/status** endpoint."
          },
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "fileType",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentsDownloadFileByIdFileType"
            },
            "required": true,
            "description": "type of file to return"
          },
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "responseType",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentsDownloadFileByIdResponseType"
            },
            "description": "encoding type of the returned file. For the moment, only \u2018base64\u2019 is implemented. Default value - \u2018base64\u2019"
          },
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "dataSource",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentsDownloadFileByIdDataSources"
            },
            "description": "a string that defines what data needs to be exported. Pass 'singleFields' to export headers or 'lineItems' for lineItems. If fileType is avs, this field will be ignored. By default is set to 'singleFields'"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentsDownloadFileByIdResponse"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "**The request was successful.** Returns object with key 'files' that contains array of requested files. Array ussually contains one item but for *avs* fileTypes it contains 2 items, one for avs file of chosen version and second one for pdf file of the document. Every object that represents the file contains two keys:\n  * `data` - key with a string in requested encoding\n  * `fileName` - key with a string that contains file name with extension\n"
          },
          "404": {
            "content": {
              "aplication/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                },
                "example": {
                  "statusCode": 404,
                  "name": "Error",
                  "message": "Document with id 7 not found"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "**The request was not successful.** It may happen for the following reasons:\n  * passed unimplemented response type\n  * document with passed id couldn\u2019t be found or this document is not Ready for Export\n"
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "**The request was not successful**. Unauthorized request has been sent.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/documents/documentsByRequestsForPeriod": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "get requests for period with statuses and files for documents",
        "tags": [
          "Document Endpoints"
        ],
        "description": "## WARNING! The endpoint has been officially deprecated. Please use a /v2 version of this endpoint.\nThis method combines three other endpoints: **/v2/requests/requestsForPeriod**, **/documents/{documentId}/file**, **/documents/status**. Successful response returns all requests and their statuses, based on passed filters, created files based on passed file type for all documents from this requests\n",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "in": "header",
            "name": "Content-Type",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": [
                "application/json"
              ]
            },
            "required": true
          },
          {
            "name": "startDate",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "unix timestamp of the start date in milliseconds",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RequestsForPeriodStartDate"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "endDate",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "unix timestamp of the end date in milliseconds",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RequestsForPeriodEndDate"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "source",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "a string that indicates source of requests",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RequestsForPeriodSource"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "status",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "a string that indicates status of requests",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RequestsForPeriodStatus"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "fileType",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "type of file to return",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentsDownloadFileByIdFileType"
            },
            "required": true
          },
          {
            "name": "responseType",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "encoding type of the returned file. For the moment, only \u2018base64\u2019 is implemented. Default value - \u2018base64\u2019",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentsDownloadFileByIdResponseType"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "dataSource",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "a string that defines what data needs to be exported. Pass 'singleFields' to export headers or 'lineItems' for lineItems. If fileType is avs, this field will be ignored. By default is set to 'singleFields'",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentsDownloadFileByIdDataSources"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "tag",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Returns documents with the specified tag for all requests",
            "schema": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentsDownloadFileByIdTag"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/documentsByRequestsForPeriodResponse"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "**The request was successful** Returns array of objects. Every object equals to object from `/document/status` endpoint except documents.files field, that is equal to `/documents/{documentId}/file` return value\n"
          },
          "412": {
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                },
                "example": {
                  "statusCode": 412,
                  "name": "Error",
                  "message": "A lot of requested documents: 235. Please change filters to decrease document amount to 200 or use other api methods"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "**The request was not successful** The amount of documents with passed filters is more than server's limit\n"
          },
          "404": {
            "content": {
              "aplication/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                },
                "example": {
                  "statusCode": 404,
                  "name": "Error",
                  "message": "Unknown status: verifiet"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "**The request was not successful.** It may happen for the following reasons:\n  * passed unimplemented response type\n  * passed uncorrect request source or status\n"
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "**The request was not successful**. Unauthorized request has been sent.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Error"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/v2/documents/{documentId}/file": {
